Let him punch himself out.

01:15:20.182 --> 01:15:22.241
Take him to the body, right? Get inside.

01:15:22.384 --> 01:15:25.148
Switch stances like you're gonna
work his right, hit him on the left.

01:15:25.287 --> 01:15:27.221
You ain't me. All right?
You can't be me.

01:15:27.356 --> 01:15:28.983
- Careful. Switch outside...
- You had a hard enough time

01:15:29.124 --> 01:15:30.819
being you when you had
your fuckin' chance,

01:15:30.959 --> 01:15:34.417
and that's why you're in here.
I'll fight Sanchez the way I fight.

01:15:34.563 --> 01:15:37.123
I'm talking about the way
you fight, you moron!

01:15:38.534 --> 01:15:41.367
Yeah, you know I'm right!
He knows I'm right. All right.

01:15:44.840 --> 01:15:46.273
He knows I'm right.

01:15:49.811 --> 01:15:55.249
<i>Ward's record: 29 wins,</i>
<i>seven losses so far, 20 KOs.</i>

01:15:55.384 --> 01:15:58.717
<i>He's been a little better since</i>
<i>he refocused himself on the sport,</i>

01:15:58.854 --> 01:16:00.378
<i>as JB pointed out.</i>

01:16:05.928 --> 01:16:10.422
Now, here's Ward's opponent,
Alfonso Sanchez, out of Tijuana, Mexico.

01:16:10.566 --> 01:16:15.697
<i>You see the record: 16 wins,</i>
<i>15 KOs, eight first-round KOs.</i>

01:16:15.837 --> 01:16:17.600
<i>There's Mike Toma,</i>
<i>the promoter of the fight,</i>

01:16:17.739 --> 01:16:19.366
<i>who has a lot invested in Sanchez.</i>

01:16:19.508 --> 01:16:21.135
And he says that Sanchez is

01:16:21.276 --> 01:16:25.576
one of the most talented young
prospects in the sport of boxing.

01:16:34.790 --> 01:16:39.784
This is really one of
the saddest kinds of fights in boxing.

01:16:39.928 --> 01:16:42.624
- Get out of the corner!
- Micky Ward is 31 years old,

01:16:42.764 --> 01:16:45.790
he's here because he needs the money,
he's taking a beating...

01:16:45.934 --> 01:16:48.198
And my point is
that he doesn't really have to sit here

01:16:48.337 --> 01:16:50.999
and take this beating.
He can do something about it.

01:16:51.139 --> 01:16:53.232
Which is what?
Have his corner throw in the towel?

01:16:53.375 --> 01:16:55.400
- Or fight back.
- Get back.

01:16:57.779 --> 01:16:58.768
You can see his power.

01:16:58.914 --> 01:17:00.973
Every time he hits Ward,
he backs him up.

01:17:01.116 --> 01:17:03.050
How about taking points away from him?

01:17:04.119 --> 01:17:06.019
<i>Larry, unless</i>
<i>the referee does, you can't.</i>

01:17:06.154 --> 01:17:07.678
<i>The referee should just go</i>
<i>ahead and stop this fight.</i>

01:17:07.823 --> 01:17:11.350
<i>He knows that Micky doesn't want</i>
<i>to be here. I wouldn't even make...</i>

01:17:11.493 --> 01:17:13.586
He's fightin' scared, Dick.

01:17:13.729 --> 01:17:15.822
Runnin' away, not hittin' back.

01:17:15.964 --> 01:17:19.593
<i>Oh, Jesus. He's gonna get hurt.</i>

01:17:19.735 --> 01:17:21.726
<i>Doing that same old shit.</i>

01:17:21.870 --> 01:17:24.202
<i>They never seen such</i>
<i>an embarrassing performance.</i>

01:17:24.339 --> 01:17:26.432
He's doing what I told him, Ma.
He's doing what I told him.

01:17:26.575 --> 01:17:28.270
Don't worry about it.
He's doing what I told him.

01:17:28.410 --> 01:17:31.277
Micky Ward, showing nothing
but respect.

01:17:31.413 --> 01:17:33.005
What are you runnin' around for?
Stop running around!

01:17:33.148 --> 01:17:36.208
Shut the fuck up, Sal!
Shut the fuck up!

01:17:36.351 --> 01:17:38.717
I don't know what you're doing, Micky.
Want to fuckin' tell me?

01:17:38.854 --> 01:17:40.082
'Cause I don't know what you're doing.

01:17:40.222 --> 01:17:42.747
We have lost all five rounds,
is that what you want?

01:17:42.891 --> 01:17:45.223
Dreadful.
This is dreadful, dreadful stuff.

01:17:45.360 --> 01:17:47.988
You gotta show me something soon,
Mick, or I'm gonna stop the fight.

01:17:48.130 --> 01:17:49.256
Now they're gonna stop the fight, Micky.

01:17:49.398 --> 01:17:51.332
He's gotta go inside, Ma.

01:17:51.466 --> 01:17:53.627
He's gotta take it to the body.
He's gotta.

01:17:53.769 --> 01:17:54.997
Come on, get your punches up...

01:17:55.137 --> 01:17:57.367
- Don't stop the fight.
- They're gonna stop this fight.

01:17:57.506 --> 01:17:59.701
Then you gotta do something, baby.

01:17:59.841 --> 01:18:01.502
That's not what we talked about, Micky.

01:18:01.643 --> 01:18:04.703
We had a plan and you're
not doing it. Now, let's go.

01:18:04.846 --> 01:18:05.904
All right, Micky.

01:18:06.048 --> 01:18:09.984
You've lost the first five rounds.
What's the next strategy gonna be?

01:18:10.118 --> 01:18:13.884
Double right hand by Sanchez,
then a triple left hook.

01:18:14.022 --> 01:18:17.014
A couple of the left hooks landed
flush on the cheek of Micky Ward.

01:18:17.159 --> 01:18:19.457
Ward tying Sanchez up.

01:18:19.594 --> 01:18:21.425
Very curious performance
by Micky Ward.

01:18:21.563 --> 01:18:22.894
Come on, Micky, come on!

01:18:23.031 --> 01:18:25.864
Ward seems...
trying to land one big shot

01:18:26.001 --> 01:18:28.265
to change Sanchez's mind...

01:18:28.403 --> 01:18:30.098
And he's beginning to open up.

01:18:30.238 --> 01:18:32.798
Taking advantage of more and more
opportunities to get close to Ward

01:18:32.941 --> 01:18:34.408
and throw against a fighter...

01:18:34.543 --> 01:18:35.567
Time!

01:18:35.711 --> 01:18:38.043
...who's not defending himself
by punching.

01:18:38.814 --> 01:18:41.146
Sanchez is gonna try
to end this fight.

01:18:47.723 --> 01:18:49.588
- What are you doing? Come on!
- That's it.

01:18:50.625 --> 01:18:51.990
Good boy!

01:18:53.361 --> 01:18:54.623
He's down on an uppercut!

01:18:58.834 --> 01:19:02.326
- Nicely thrown left uppercut inside.
...three, four, five...

01:19:02.471 --> 01:19:05.736
And right after Ward threw
a pretty good right hand.

01:19:05.874 --> 01:19:08.843
Mick, you all right?
Come to me. Come to me.

01:19:08.977 --> 01:19:10.877
This is a fight
that should be stopped.

01:19:12.247 --> 01:19:13.771
Come on, head, body, head.

01:19:16.618 --> 01:19:18.108
This is not professional.

01:19:18.253 --> 01:19:20.016
That's exactly what I'm saying.

01:19:20.155 --> 01:19:23.181
- Punch him! You gotta punch!
- Someone should pay me to watch this.

01:19:23.325 --> 01:19:26.317
Come on, man! Head, body, head!

01:19:28.063 --> 01:19:29.360
That was a good body shot by Ward.

01:19:29.498 --> 01:19:31.989
That was good.
Maybe it'll turn him around.

01:19:32.134 --> 01:19:34.295
Maybe. I'm talking about if I...

01:19:35.637 --> 01:19:38.538
Sanchez drops
like he's shot! Oh, my God!

01:19:38.673 --> 01:19:42.769
The most unlikely
knockout you have ever seen.

01:19:42.911 --> 01:19:45.812
That was a kidney shot,
the kind of kidney shot...

01:19:45.947 --> 01:19:47.847
...nine, ten!

01:19:50.452 --> 01:19:52.750
I still don't believe
what I just saw.

01:19:56.691 --> 01:19:58.886
Oh, Micky won!

01:20:01.463 --> 01:20:03.829
Now, did Micky Ward
just make idiots of us all

01:20:03.965 --> 01:20:07.992
with a spectacular piece of strategy?
Take another look. Amazing.

01:20:08.136 --> 01:20:10.764
<i>A brilliant win in the career</i>
<i>of Micky Ward out of Lowell, Mass.</i>

01:20:10.906 --> 01:20:14.205
<i>Unbelievable defeat</i>
<i>at the hands of Micky Ward,</i>

01:20:14.342 --> 01:20:18.779
<i>who had all but given away the first</i>
<i>half-dozen rounds of the bout.</i>

01:20:18.914 --> 01:20:21.041
I think what Micky did was he recognized

01:20:21.183 --> 01:20:22.980
that he'd hurt the guy
with the body shot.

01:20:23.118 --> 01:20:25.916
Micky's a better fighter than that to
not be runnin' from that guy like that.

01:20:26.054 --> 01:20:28.045
Theater of the unexpected.

01:20:28.190 --> 01:20:30.556
Hey, you never know
what can happen, right?

01:20:30.692 --> 01:20:32.159
Never give up in this game, right?
Never give up.

01:20:33.161 --> 01:20:34.753
You can't make it up, folks.

01:20:34.896 --> 01:20:36.386
You hear what he said?

01:20:36.531 --> 01:20:38.226
He said, " You can't give up
in this game."

01:20:38.366 --> 01:20:41.301
Well, maybe Micky Ward
heard me say you should stop this fight

01:20:41.436 --> 01:20:43.165
and he went out and stopped it.

01:20:43.839 --> 01:20:46.501
- Right there. Right there.
- Yeah! I can't believe it.

01:20:46.641 --> 01:20:49.508
I'm lookin' over, and I'm thinkin'
to myself like they were thinkin'

01:20:49.644 --> 01:20:50.872
This thing is over.

01:20:51.012 --> 01:20:52.946
But I tell you what, if you
looked at the commentators,

01:20:53.081 --> 01:20:55.709
they started to take their headsets off
before he was even counted out.

01:20:55.851 --> 01:20:57.216
They just wanted to get out of there.

01:20:57.352 --> 01:21:00.048
Mick, Mick.
I just spoke to Mike Toma.

01:21:00.188 --> 01:21:02.554
- He told me something very interesting.
- Holy shit, what?

01:21:02.691 --> 01:21:04.056
He just told me,

01:21:04.192 --> 01:21:06.752
had Sanchez won tonight,
he would've gotten the title shot.

01:21:06.895 --> 01:21:09.989
- Holy Christ, that's beautiful.
- Why? Why is that beautiful?

01:21:10.131 --> 01:21:14.727
- A title shot. Mick gets the shot.
- Micky gets the shot!

01:21:14.870 --> 01:21:18.271
- Are you kidding me?
- Are you sure about that?

01:21:18.406 --> 01:21:21.637
I just spoke to the guy. Mike!
Come here, Mike. Look, tell these guys.

01:21:21.776 --> 01:21:23.573
- Hey, Mike Toma. Thank you.
- Congratulations.

01:21:23.712 --> 01:21:26.806
You're not a stepping stone anymore.
I always knew you had the talent.

01:21:26.948 --> 01:21:29.781
That was a hell of a strategy, wearing
him down and taking it to the body.

01:21:29.918 --> 01:21:32.887
Thirty years in the business,
I'd never seen a knockout like that.

01:21:33.021 --> 01:21:34.511
Larry Merchant was writing
your obituary,

01:21:34.656 --> 01:21:35.953
and Sanchez drops
like he's shot with a gun.

01:21:36.091 --> 01:21:37.854
Where'd you get that?

01:21:37.993 --> 01:21:39.358
That's the first thing
my brother taught me.

01:21:39.494 --> 01:21:40.927
Tap 'em to the head,
ding 'em to the body.

01:21:41.062 --> 01:21:43.087
- That's a hell of a body shot.
- Thank you.

01:21:43.231 --> 01:21:46.291
- You ready for a title shot?
- I ain't gettin' no younger.

01:21:46.935 --> 01:21:49.267
Thanks, Mr. Toma. Thank you.

01:21:49.404 --> 01:21:51.304
He's ready. You're ready, aren't ya?

01:21:52.274 --> 01:21:54.902
Shea Neary in London
for the title.

01:21:55.043 --> 01:21:56.977
Are you kidding,
we got some celebrating to do.

01:21:57.112 --> 01:21:58.511
- Yeah, I think so.
- Thank you so much.

01:21:58.647 --> 01:22:01.138
- Gonna have a great champ in my boy.
- Thank you, Mr. Toma.

01:22:03.718 --> 01:22:05.709
It's what your brother
would've always wanted.

01:22:05.854 --> 01:22:07.583
He's not even gonna be there.

01:22:33.648 --> 01:22:36.708
- Hey!
- Daddy!

01:22:36.851 --> 01:22:38.876
- Come here, buddy.
- Daddy, Daddy!

01:22:39.988 --> 01:22:42.149
Good to see you!

01:22:43.591 --> 01:22:47.857
That's a good hug!
That's a good hug! Yeah!

01:22:47.996 --> 01:22:50.328
- Sweetheart.
- Hey, Ma.

01:22:50.465 --> 01:22:55.027
Oh, you look so good. Oh, my God.

01:23:02.477 --> 01:23:05.275
- You have clean teeth.
- I do! Look at my teeth!

01:23:06.081 --> 01:23:08.015
I got new teeth. Everything.

01:23:08.149 --> 01:23:09.480
How you think I look?

01:23:09.617 --> 01:23:11.744
- Good.
- Yeah?

01:23:24.599 --> 01:23:26.726
Cake and more cake.

01:23:26.868 --> 01:23:29.462
- Ice cream?
- Ice cream and cake.

01:23:29.604 --> 01:23:32.198
Ice cream and cake and cake. Right?

01:23:32.340 --> 01:23:35.503
Ice cream, cake and cake.
Ice cream, cake and cake...

01:23:35.643 --> 01:23:37.201
Quacka!

01:23:42.384 --> 01:23:43.874
Ma.

01:23:56.831 --> 01:23:59.857
- They gave you some new teeth, huh?
- Yeah.

01:24:04.272 --> 01:24:06.604
Hey, Georgie. What, they let
you outta the house now?

01:24:06.741 --> 01:24:09.266
- Yeah.
- Lettin' him outta the house, Ma?

01:24:09.411 --> 01:24:11.436
Hey, look, I want you
to meet Sal Lonano.

01:24:18.286 --> 01:24:20.254
How you doing, Dicky?

01:24:22.290 --> 01:24:23.757
Let's spar.

01:24:31.966 --> 01:24:33.433
Hey, Charlene.

01:24:58.660 --> 01:25:00.321
Welcome back!

01:25:00.462 --> 01:25:03.124
It's supposed to be a surprise.
You're late.

01:25:04.232 --> 01:25:06.462
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:25:06.601 --> 01:25:10.093
Mick, I can't even tell you, being in
this smelly-ass locker room. You know?

01:25:10.238 --> 01:25:12.900
Being back with you,
this is what got me through.

01:25:13.041 --> 01:25:17.410
- You look good. Your eyes are clear.
- Yeah. You know...

01:25:18.613 --> 01:25:21.343
...Alice says prison might've
been the best thing for me.

01:25:21.483 --> 01:25:24.884
Got me clean. Got me clear. Up here.

01:25:25.987 --> 01:25:27.955
It's a beautiful thing, Dick.

01:25:29.691 --> 01:25:33.525
- I gotta talk to you about something.
- Yeah.

01:25:33.661 --> 01:25:37.153
Look at this locker.
The old locker.

01:25:37.298 --> 01:25:38.925
I love it. Fuckin' love it.

01:25:40.969 --> 01:25:44.427
I made a promise to them
I wouldn't work with you again.

01:25:54.282 --> 01:25:58.013
I had to. After everything
that happened, I'm sorry.

01:26:02.957 --> 01:26:05.323
You stickin' to that?

01:26:06.761 --> 01:26:11.357
I'm glad you're back. You look good.

01:26:11.499 --> 01:26:14.730
I don't know what else to say.

01:26:21.709 --> 01:26:24.007
- Mick, you fuckin' kidding me?
- No, I'm not.

01:26:28.783 --> 01:26:31.752
- Oh, hey, Mick.
- Come on, come on!

01:26:31.886 --> 01:26:35.982
You gotta... Ma. You gotta
do this at home. Please?

01:26:36.124 --> 01:26:37.819
What are you talkin' about?
What's the matter?

01:26:37.959 --> 01:26:40.018
Mom, please?

01:26:40.161 --> 01:26:42.493
All right, girls. Let's pack it up.

01:26:42.630 --> 01:26:44.063
I know. We'll see him at home.

01:27:06.387 --> 01:27:08.753
- What the hell...?
- Would you please pack it up?

01:27:08.890 --> 01:27:10.289
- Why?
- Let's get it put away.

01:27:11.059 --> 01:27:13.892
If that's what Micky wants,
we're gonna put it away.

01:27:14.028 --> 01:27:16.258
- There's your brother.
- Dicky...

01:27:16.397 --> 01:27:19.594
- How ya doing?
- Micky?

01:27:24.272 --> 01:27:26.763
That's nice. That's nice.

01:27:26.908 --> 01:27:28.375
We've been working on it
for two weeks.

01:27:28.509 --> 01:27:30.443
Sherri, come on, stop it.

01:27:30.578 --> 01:27:32.045
All right, girls,
come on, let's go home.

01:27:32.180 --> 01:27:34.546
It's not the time to do this,
obviously. Come on.

01:27:34.682 --> 01:27:38.948
You stay here.
What the hell's going on?

01:27:39.087 --> 01:27:41.578
- What's going on?
- We ain't gonna work together.

01:27:42.624 --> 01:27:44.387
He don't want me to work with him.

01:27:44.525 --> 01:27:46.618
What're you talking about?

01:27:46.761 --> 01:27:48.820
That's not right.

01:27:48.963 --> 01:27:52.455
Micky never would've won
Sanchez without Dicky.

01:27:52.600 --> 01:27:54.830
That's fuckin' bullshit! Take it back!

01:27:54.969 --> 01:27:57.335
Hey, hey, hey, hey. Don't you fuckin'
talk to my mother that way.

01:27:57.472 --> 01:27:58.461
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you!

01:27:58.606 --> 01:28:00.198
Take 'em home.

01:28:02.243 --> 01:28:03.676
Why don't you ask Micky?

01:28:04.612 --> 01:28:06.876
If we're gonna train, they gotta go.

01:28:07.015 --> 01:28:08.949
They gotta go, Mick, come on.

01:28:09.951 --> 01:28:13.648
Ask him, George. Ask him if he would've
won Sanchez without his brother?

01:28:13.788 --> 01:28:15.449
Hey, take him outside, all right?

01:28:17.659 --> 01:28:19.991
No, I wouldn't have won Sanchez
if it wasn't for Dicky.

01:28:21.129 --> 01:28:22.323
How can you say that to O'Keefe?

01:28:22.463 --> 01:28:23.953
Because it's true.

01:28:24.799 --> 01:28:26.562
I went with that game plan,
it wasn't working.

01:28:26.701 --> 01:28:28.726
So I went back to what
I learned with Dicky.

01:28:28.870 --> 01:28:31.771
And I wouldn't have won without you,
either, O'Keefe, OK?

01:28:32.607 --> 01:28:35.474
I mean, you know that.
We worked hard. You got me ready.

01:28:35.610 --> 01:28:38.101
You got your confidence
and your focus from O'Keefe,

01:28:38.246 --> 01:28:41.477
and from Sal and
your father and from me.

01:28:43.051 --> 01:28:45.246
- Dicky's a junk bag.
- Hey.

01:28:45.386 --> 01:28:46.546
He's a junk bag!

01:28:46.688 --> 01:28:48.280
- Fuck you, Charlene.
- Fuck you.

01:28:48.423 --> 01:28:49.856
- I'm eight months sober.
- Oh, yeah,

01:28:49.991 --> 01:28:51.788
and I'm sure you're gonna need
something now that you're out.

01:28:51.926 --> 01:28:53.723
"Oh, my back. Oh, my back."

01:28:53.861 --> 01:28:56.193
- Fuck you always picking on me for?
- No, fuck you!

01:28:56.331 --> 01:28:58.094
And what about O'Keefe?
We're in the same boat.

01:28:58.232 --> 01:29:00.860
One day at a fucking time, right,
O'Keefe? You know what I mean?

01:29:01.002 --> 01:29:02.401
What, it's all right
for him to be here?

01:29:02.537 --> 01:29:04.903
Why am I the fuckin' problem?
I'm his blood, I'm his family!

01:29:05.039 --> 01:29:07.064
- You are the problem!
- I'm the one fighting, OK?

01:29:07.208 --> 01:29:09.676
Not you, not you, and not you.

01:29:11.112 --> 01:29:13.046
- I know what I need.
- And you need Dicky?

01:29:13.181 --> 01:29:14.705
I want Dicky back.

01:29:15.917 --> 01:29:18.215
And I want you, Charlene.
And I want O'Keefe.

01:29:18.353 --> 01:29:20.753
I want my family.
What's wrong with that?

01:29:22.657 --> 01:29:24.648
It's not the deal we made, baby.

01:29:24.792 --> 01:29:26.282
She's right, Micky.
That's not the deal.

01:29:26.427 --> 01:29:30.386
It wasn't the deal.
Come on, you can't do this to us.

01:29:30.531 --> 01:29:32.192
- You sound like them now.
- I sound like them now?

01:29:32.333 --> 01:29:33.960
- Yeah, you sound like them.
- You sound like them.

01:29:34.102 --> 01:29:35.569
How could I do this to you?
"You can't do that to us.

01:29:35.703 --> 01:29:39.332
He can't do that to us."
You sound like them.

01:29:39.474 --> 01:29:41.101
You should fuckin' listen to yourself.

01:29:41.242 --> 01:29:43.802
You sound like them and maybe
this is where you belong.

01:29:43.945 --> 01:29:45.412
That's the way you love him?

01:29:45.546 --> 01:29:47.571
- Charlene!
- Come on!

01:29:47.715 --> 01:29:50.980
- You wanted your brother? Good luck.
- O'Keefe, come on.

01:29:51.119 --> 01:29:53.815
- Mickey.
- Mickey.

01:29:56.924 --> 01:29:59.415
Come on, everything
happens for a reason.

01:30:00.261 --> 01:30:05.426
You know? Maybe it's for the best.
God has a plan.

01:30:07.869 --> 01:30:09.666
Wanna spar with your brother?

01:30:16.344 --> 01:30:18.471
Dick Eklund, pride of Lowell!

01:30:19.414 --> 01:30:21.507
Watching that for years, huh?

01:30:24.485 --> 01:30:25.577
Micky, Micky!

01:30:25.720 --> 01:30:28.245
Whoa, hey!
What the hell are you doing?

01:30:28.389 --> 01:30:29.651
Micky!

01:30:29.791 --> 01:30:31.691
- Daddy! Daddy, Daddy!
- For crying out loud!

01:30:31.826 --> 01:30:33.384
Take that baby out of here.

01:30:33.528 --> 01:30:35.120
I told you take him away
ten minutes ago!

01:30:36.097 --> 01:30:39.396
Sweetheart, you all right?
You OK? Your back?

01:30:39.534 --> 01:30:42.833
What are you doing?
What's the matter with you?

01:30:42.970 --> 01:30:46.701
Can this be my fight, Alice?
Just once?

01:30:46.841 --> 01:30:50.402
Maybe just this one time
not for Dicky?

01:30:50.545 --> 01:30:52.604
I know you think he's coming back.

01:30:52.747 --> 01:30:54.647
He's 40 years old and doesn't
have a tooth in his head

01:30:54.782 --> 01:30:57.478
- that's his fuckin' own.
- I'll go fuckin' ten rounds.

01:30:57.618 --> 01:30:59.745
Let your brother talk
for a minute here, all right?

01:30:59.887 --> 01:31:01.684
- What are you sayin' sweetheart?
- I'm Shea Neary...

01:31:01.823 --> 01:31:04.883
Shut up before I bust your
fuckin' head open, Dicky.

01:31:05.026 --> 01:31:07.961
- Hey, hey...
- What're you gonna do? I'm Shea Neary.

01:31:08.095 --> 01:31:09.460
You want me to bust
your fuckin' head open?

01:31:09.597 --> 01:31:10.996
Come on, come on! George, please!

01:31:11.132 --> 01:31:13.259
- Dicky!
- Please! What are you saying?

01:31:13.401 --> 01:31:16.859
- Tell me what you're saying.
- This is supposed to be my fight.

01:31:17.004 --> 01:31:19.564
This is my shot at a title.
I won't get another one after this.

01:31:19.707 --> 01:31:21.197
- Am I being selfish?
- No.

01:31:21.342 --> 01:31:24.140
Am I saying, "Micky, Micky, Micky?"
You know what? If I am, I'm sorry.

01:31:24.278 --> 01:31:25.745
I thought I was fightin'
for the championship.

01:31:25.880 --> 01:31:27.905
And I thought you
were my mother, too.

01:31:29.250 --> 01:31:31.275
I am your mother.

01:31:32.153 --> 01:31:33.711
Yeah, Ma.

01:31:36.090 --> 01:31:40.254
Mick, I'm sorry. I had no idea
you felt like that, all right?

01:31:40.394 --> 01:31:42.555
If I made mistakes,
I'm gonna be better.

01:31:43.731 --> 01:31:48.100
I don't wanna hurt you.
I am so sorry. I'm sorry.

01:31:53.908 --> 01:31:55.205
Dicky!

01:31:55.343 --> 01:31:56.708
Stay with him.

01:31:57.678 --> 01:32:01.444
Dicky... Dicky!

01:32:06.988 --> 01:32:08.979
- Dicky!
- Gotta do something.

01:32:09.123 --> 01:32:11.648
Dicky, wait, come on!

01:32:11.792 --> 01:32:15.922
- Micky wants you! I want you!
- I gotta do something.

01:32:16.063 --> 01:32:18.327
I know what that means.
Don't do this!

01:32:46.761 --> 01:32:48.353
Hey, Chan.

01:32:53.067 --> 01:32:55.558
- What's going on?
- Hey, Dicky.

01:32:57.505 --> 01:32:58.938
Hey, Dicky's back!

01:32:59.073 --> 01:33:00.665
Hey!

01:33:02.643 --> 01:33:03.940
Look at you!

01:33:04.078 --> 01:33:07.206
What's up, my boy?
How you doing? Good to see you, man.

01:33:07.348 --> 01:33:10.875
- You look good. Welcome back.
- Yeah, you're looking good.

01:33:11.018 --> 01:33:12.679
- Great.
- Good to see ya.

01:33:12.820 --> 01:33:15.345
- Welcome home.
- Hi, honey.

01:33:17.158 --> 01:33:19.490
What's up, man?
You're looking good.

01:33:19.627 --> 01:33:21.959
- Wanna head upstairs?
- Dicky's back.

01:33:22.096 --> 01:33:24.462
- Hi, Dicky. We're gonna party.
- Go upstairs, man?

01:33:28.436 --> 01:33:31.303
- Go upstairs, take a while?
- We missed you!

01:33:31.439 --> 01:33:34.670
- Let's go, buddy.
- Come on, Dicky.

01:33:38.179 --> 01:33:42.138
- Make for a little party for you...
- Hey, come back.

01:33:42.984 --> 01:33:45.418
- What the fuck's that all about?
- What the hell was that?

01:34:01.369 --> 01:34:04.031
Charlene? It's Dicky.

01:34:05.806 --> 01:34:08.036
<i>Get off my porch,</i>
<i>you piece of shit.</i>

01:34:10.411 --> 01:34:12.038
<i>How fuckin' dare you...</i>

01:34:13.481 --> 01:34:14.675
<i>... cocksucker...</i>

01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:16.609
<i>... fuckin'...</i>

01:34:20.054 --> 01:34:21.385
You're a fuckin' asshole, Dicky.

01:34:21.522 --> 01:34:23.422
I want you off my fuckin' porch!

01:34:23.557 --> 01:34:26.617
Why don't you just fuckin'
come down here and talk to me?

01:34:26.761 --> 01:34:29.093
Such an asshole, coming to my
fucking house. You piece of shit!

01:34:29.230 --> 01:34:30.788
- Standing on my porch...
- Charlene...

01:34:30.931 --> 01:34:34.560
It's not fuckin' lady-like to be
shoutin' in the street like this.

01:34:34.702 --> 01:34:36.431
You're such a fuckin' cocksucker
coming over here.

01:34:36.570 --> 01:34:38.401
- Please?
- Oh, yeah, you think I fuckin' care?

01:34:38.539 --> 01:34:41.770
- Come on, just fuckin'...
- Get off my fuckin' porch, Dicky!

01:34:41.909 --> 01:34:45.811
Would you just fuckin'
come down here... and talk to me?

01:34:55.389 --> 01:34:58.119
What kind of dog is that?
Is that a Cocker Spaniel?

01:35:03.764 --> 01:35:05.459
All right, I know you
can't fuckin' stand me.

01:35:05.599 --> 01:35:06.759
Really, what makes you say that?

01:35:06.901 --> 01:35:10.393
I ain't got no use for you, either.
All right? But my brother loves ya.

01:35:10.538 --> 01:35:12.699
And you can't just
run away because of me.

01:35:12.840 --> 01:35:14.808
He don't deserve that. All right?

01:35:14.942 --> 01:35:17.433
So I will quit if you want me to quit.

01:35:17.578 --> 01:35:20.411
- You're full of shit.
- I swear to God.

01:35:20.548 --> 01:35:22.516
I will quit if it means
you'll come back, all right?

01:35:22.650 --> 01:35:24.277
But I want you to think about something.

01:35:24.418 --> 01:35:27.444
Micky has a chance to do
something that I never did.

01:35:27.588 --> 01:35:29.146
That in my time, I never had.

01:35:29.290 --> 01:35:32.350
"Oh, yeah, my big chance
was with Sugar Ray Leonard.

01:35:32.493 --> 01:35:34.427
I'm so great.
I'm the pride of fuckin' Lowell.

01:35:34.562 --> 01:35:36.553
Oh, yeah, I fought Sugar Ray Leonard."
I've heard it.

01:35:36.697 --> 01:35:37.925
I came here to make things right.

01:35:38.065 --> 01:35:39.464
- OK, let's make things right.
- Yeah.

01:35:39.600 --> 01:35:43.866
Number one: You didn't knock down
Sugar Ray Leonard. He tripped.

01:35:45.506 --> 01:35:48.134
I was in the ring. Don't you think
I know what really happened that day?

01:35:48.275 --> 01:35:51.608
All right? What have you
ever done with your life?

01:35:51.746 --> 01:35:53.771
- I like my life.
- Yeah, what you ever done with it?

01:35:53.914 --> 01:35:56.644
- I like my life now, Dicky.
- What have you done with your life?

01:35:56.784 --> 01:35:58.183
You're a college dropout, Charlene.

01:35:58.319 --> 01:36:01.117
You're just a little bar girl.
Your life sucks.

01:36:02.590 --> 01:36:05.650
All right. I drank too much.

01:36:05.793 --> 01:36:07.852
I worked in a lot of bars.

01:36:07.995 --> 01:36:10.987
And I ruined a lot of opportunities, but
I'm trying to do something better here.

01:36:11.132 --> 01:36:13.498
- And so is Micky.
- And so am I.

01:36:15.302 --> 01:36:20.137
And he needs me. You heard him.
And I know he needs you.

01:36:23.244 --> 01:36:25.337
What is that blue shit on your arm?

01:36:26.547 --> 01:36:28.174
It's icing.

01:36:31.385 --> 01:36:35.719
OK. I'll see ya in Micky's corner.
Otherwise, go fuck yourself.

01:36:35.856 --> 01:36:37.790
- It's a deal.
- All right? It's a deal.

01:36:50.337 --> 01:36:52.601
We worked it out for you. Ask her.

01:36:54.275 --> 01:36:57.836
Good. Go get O'Keefe back, too.

01:36:58.879 --> 01:37:00.642
I will.

01:37:05.920 --> 01:37:06.978
Hey, Mick...

01:37:09.390 --> 01:37:12.848
You think I knocked down
Sugar Ray Leonard?

01:37:12.993 --> 01:37:16.759
Went ten rounds. One of the best
ever and he couldn't hurt you.

01:37:16.897 --> 01:37:18.831
You were my hero.

01:37:19.466 --> 01:37:21.263
I was.

01:37:22.803 --> 01:37:24.327
I was.

01:37:29.510 --> 01:37:31.535
I'm sorry.

01:37:31.679 --> 01:37:33.237
You are?

01:38:51.158 --> 01:38:53.251
There's a press conference downstairs.

01:38:54.128 --> 01:38:55.686
Come on, let's go.

01:38:56.196 --> 01:38:57.322
Spot of tea, mate!

01:38:57.464 --> 01:39:01.594
Neary: Ten stone... six pound.

01:39:08.242 --> 01:39:12.303
Ward: Ten stone... six pound.

01:39:13.447 --> 01:39:16.211
Hey, Micky, Micky Ward!
We have a question over here.

01:39:18.452 --> 01:39:21.421
- How you been training?
- I train, I train hard.

01:39:21.555 --> 01:39:23.819
Shea's 22 and 0.
He's never been knocked down.

01:39:23.958 --> 01:39:26.290
- That's gonna change tomorrow.
- In fact, we expected

01:39:26.427 --> 01:39:27.655
a much better fighter.

01:39:28.562 --> 01:39:30.462
I'm just grateful to be here
and have the opportunity.

01:39:30.597 --> 01:39:32.064
Thank you guys for the shot.

01:39:32.199 --> 01:39:36.295
Shea, who do you respect as a fighter?
And who would you like to fight next?

01:39:37.538 --> 01:39:39.870
I plan on moving right
through Micky Ward tomorrow.

01:39:40.007 --> 01:39:42.100
Moving on to other great fighters,
like Gatti.

01:39:42.242 --> 01:39:44.506
Yeah, I believe Gatti and I
would make a great match.

01:39:44.645 --> 01:39:46.135
Are you scared, Mr. Ward?

01:39:59.259 --> 01:40:02.524
And now, ladies and
gentlemen, 12 rounds of boxing

01:40:02.663 --> 01:40:08.295
for the WBU Welterweight
Championship of the World!

01:40:12.272 --> 01:40:13.398
I can't see!

01:40:14.875 --> 01:40:18.276
<i>Here I go again on my own</i>

01:40:19.947 --> 01:40:23.508
<i>Goin' down the only road</i>
<i>I've ever known</i>

01:40:25.185 --> 01:40:29.451
<i>Like a drifter</i>
<i>I was born to walk alone</i>

01:40:30.824 --> 01:40:34.351
- Hey, fellas, let's go.
<i>- I made up my mind</i>

01:40:36.930 --> 01:40:39.797
<i>I ain't wasting no more time</i>

01:40:41.201 --> 01:40:45.604
<i>Here I go again on my own</i>

01:40:46.807 --> 01:40:50.470
<i>Going down the only road</i>
<i>I've ever known</i>

01:40:52.079 --> 01:40:55.708
<i>Like a drifter I was born</i>
<i>to walk alone</i>

01:40:55.849 --> 01:40:57.783
Don't listen to 'em, Mick.

01:40:58.719 --> 01:41:01.279
<i>I made up my mind</i>

01:41:03.757 --> 01:41:06.988
<i>I ain't wasting no more time...</i>

01:41:10.998 --> 01:41:13.228
And there is Micky Ward
of Lowell, Massachusetts,

01:41:13.367 --> 01:41:16.768
entering the ring. It's his
first fight outside the United States.

01:41:16.904 --> 01:41:22.900
<i>Micky Ward: 30 wins, seven losses.</i>
<i>He's gotten better recently, 20 KOs.</i>

01:41:24.244 --> 01:41:27.805
<i>And now Ward awaits his</i>
<i>opponent, Shea Neary.</i>

01:41:27.948 --> 01:41:32.749
Neary regards himself
as the European Arturo Gatti.

01:41:32.886 --> 01:41:35.514
Meaning that he is a head-on,
high-contact fighter

01:41:35.656 --> 01:41:38.489
who throws 70 punches per round.

01:41:40.060 --> 01:41:41.721
Neary's from Liverpool
and should have

01:41:41.862 --> 01:41:43.796
a huge following here tonight.

01:41:45.732 --> 01:41:50.226
Accompanied
by <i>Paint the Town Red</i> by The Mahones.

01:41:50.370 --> 01:41:53.806
Neary is the current
Welterweight Champion of the World.

01:41:53.941 --> 01:41:57.570
He is a very tough young man.
Beyond dedicated.

01:41:57.711 --> 01:42:01.545
Lives a Spartan existence.
And according to his promoters,

01:42:01.682 --> 01:42:06.085
does nothing but eat,
drink, think, fantasize...

01:42:06.220 --> 01:42:08.620
...dream of fighting.

01:42:08.755 --> 01:42:12.418
Shea Neary has had 22
professional fights and won them all.

01:42:12.559 --> 01:42:14.550
Seventeen KOs.

01:42:24.838 --> 01:42:28.467
Come out when you hear the bell.
Don't piss about. Shake hands.

01:42:28.609 --> 01:42:32.636
Both of ya... shake hands!

01:42:32.779 --> 01:42:36.613
As close as we just saw
them in the middle of the ring,

01:42:36.750 --> 01:42:39.082
- forehead to forehead,
- Did you see that?

01:42:39.219 --> 01:42:44.851
That's how close we expect them to be
for as long as this fight goes on.

01:42:44.992 --> 01:42:46.926
Ward is a long ways from home.

01:42:47.060 --> 01:42:48.789
Don't coast in a foreign country.

01:42:48.929 --> 01:42:50.658
Well, the big challenge for Ward

01:42:50.797 --> 01:42:53.789
is to get off to a faster start
than is customary for him.

01:42:53.934 --> 01:42:57.495
Micky Ward, a notoriously
slow starter in big fights,

01:42:57.638 --> 01:43:00.072
Shea Neary, an ultra-fast starter.

01:43:00.207 --> 01:43:02.437
And that's the question
that hovers over round one.

01:43:02.576 --> 01:43:04.100
Will Ward be ready for the fight?

01:43:04.244 --> 01:43:07.680
Already, Shea Neary starts
taking it to him on the ropes!

01:43:07.814 --> 01:43:10.942
And Neary going to the body,
which is Ward's specialty.

01:43:12.252 --> 01:43:14.447
Neary bangs Ward to the body.

01:43:14.588 --> 01:43:16.453
And a big uppercut by Neary.

01:43:16.590 --> 01:43:18.820
Neary leads off with a good left jab.

01:43:18.959 --> 01:43:20.893
- Come on, Micky!
- Keeps Ward off balance,

01:43:21.028 --> 01:43:22.393
jabbing here and there.

01:43:24.431 --> 01:43:28.595
There's a good left hook
by Neary as he stepped in on Ward.

01:43:28.735 --> 01:43:33.638
Ward not able to deal with him very well
when Neary stands at range like this.

01:43:33.774 --> 01:43:35.765
- Come on!
- That's it! Get him!

01:43:35.909 --> 01:43:38.434
And a left hook
lands up top from Micky Ward.

01:43:39.613 --> 01:43:41.478
Neary digging his
own right hand to the body.

01:43:41.615 --> 01:43:43.583
They trade shots at close range.

01:43:44.918 --> 01:43:47.318
Ward, he's trying
to match Neary blow for blow

01:43:47.454 --> 01:43:52.790
and now Neary starts to come on and
take the last 30 seconds of the round...

01:43:52.926 --> 01:43:54.120
How about that?

01:43:54.261 --> 01:43:55.489
Break!

01:43:56.730 --> 01:43:59.597
Tremendous barrage in
the first minute. Just look at this.

01:43:59.733 --> 01:44:03.294
- Unbelievable.
- What a great round one!

01:44:03.437 --> 01:44:07.237
Ward is gonna have
to pick up the tempo

01:44:07.374 --> 01:44:09.467
and beat him with volumes of punching.

01:44:09.610 --> 01:44:12.704
<i>No doubt, Neary is a better boxer.</i>

01:44:15.182 --> 01:44:20.017
Four hard right hands...
Neary has belted in the last minute.

01:44:20.153 --> 01:44:23.520
Quicker than Ward,
more assertive than Ward,

01:44:23.657 --> 01:44:25.318
surer of what he wants to do.

01:44:25.459 --> 01:44:28.121
They're standing and trading shots
at the center of the ring.

01:44:28.262 --> 01:44:30.162
Ward's gonna have
to step it up a little bit more

01:44:30.297 --> 01:44:31.423
than he is right now.

01:44:31.565 --> 01:44:33.362
Micky Ward's corner
taking a real deep look

01:44:33.500 --> 01:44:34.797
at what's going on now.

01:44:34.935 --> 01:44:38.598
And his family at ringside well aware
he's stepping up in class.

01:44:38.739 --> 01:44:41.674
Ward has fallen to the pedal.
He's gotta be more aggressive.

01:44:41.808 --> 01:44:44.003
He can't just try to wait
until everything is perfect.

01:44:44.144 --> 01:44:47.136
His dominance over Micky Ward
is increasing as the fight goes on

01:44:47.281 --> 01:44:51.650
because his technical plan
was the right one and he's executing it.

01:44:51.785 --> 01:44:55.482
Punches like these make it seem...

01:44:56.323 --> 01:44:58.985
...that it's now Neary's fight.

01:45:00.494 --> 01:45:02.428
Ward hasn't been in this kind of war

01:45:02.562 --> 01:45:04.996
with this strong of fighter as Neary.

01:45:06.700 --> 01:45:10.659
They are trying
to hurt each other with every punch.

01:45:10.804 --> 01:45:15.298
They've tested each other's will,
now they're testing each other's skill.

01:45:15.442 --> 01:45:18.707
And Ward wobbled there
by a right cross from Neary!

01:45:18.845 --> 01:45:21.405
Ward hurting now. His legs are gone.

01:45:21.548 --> 01:45:25.109
Neary goes to the body
as he tries to finish Micky.

01:45:26.353 --> 01:45:28.412
Vicious body shots from Neary.

01:45:28.555 --> 01:45:32.082
And Ward still doesn't
even try to move off the ropes!

01:45:32.225 --> 01:45:34.420
I don't know if he can, Jim.

01:45:34.561 --> 01:45:36.620
He's waiting for Neary
to punch himself out.

01:45:36.763 --> 01:45:39.493
Down goes Micky Ward! He may be out.

01:45:39.633 --> 01:45:40.895
That ain't fuckin' it!

01:45:41.034 --> 01:45:44.367
- One... two...
- Come on! That's it!

01:45:45.739 --> 01:45:49.197
- That's my boy!
- Forward! Forward! Come on!

01:45:51.011 --> 01:45:53.172
Ward is out on his feet.

01:45:53.313 --> 01:45:56.282
Loser! Go back to America!

01:45:56.416 --> 01:45:59.817
- This could be it for Micky Ward.
- Dicky, give him the fuckin' stool.

01:45:59.953 --> 01:46:01.978
Charlene, will you get
the fuck outta here.

01:46:02.122 --> 01:46:04.147
He needs to fuckin' sit down!

01:46:04.825 --> 01:46:07.385
His brother's got
Ward jumping to wake up his legs.

01:46:09.296 --> 01:46:13.255
I think this could be Ward's last chance
to turn this fight around.

01:46:13.400 --> 01:46:15.459
It's Micky Ward
against the aggressiveness

01:46:15.602 --> 01:46:17.570
and clean punching of Shea Neary.

01:46:18.739 --> 01:46:22.004
If you don't have your defense up,
you can really get hurt.

01:46:22.142 --> 01:46:24.269
He's making it very
difficult for Micky Ward.

01:46:24.411 --> 01:46:27.039
I don't think he's gonna
get into it at this rate.

01:46:27.180 --> 01:46:29.375
This is a survival mode...

01:46:29.516 --> 01:46:33.316
Are you like me? Was just
good enough to fight Sugar Ray?

01:46:33.453 --> 01:46:35.011
Never had to win, did I?

01:46:35.155 --> 01:46:38.318
You gotta do more in there.
You gotta win a title.

01:46:38.458 --> 01:46:41.450
For you, for me, for Lowell.

01:46:41.595 --> 01:46:44.393
This is your time, all right?
You take it.

01:46:44.531 --> 01:46:46.465
I had my time and I blew it.
You don't have to.

01:46:46.600 --> 01:46:48.397
All right?
You fuckin' get out there,

01:46:48.535 --> 01:46:50.560
and use all the shit
that you've been through,

